headline: Jobs Data, Spending Figures, Show Worrying Side of a Resilient Economy
summary: The U.S. economy is looking in fairly good shape as the second quarter glides to a close, with reasonably modest inflation, record-high stocks, and solid GDP growth.  Emerging weakness in the labor market, however, is starting to test whether that resilience can extend into the back half of the year.  Hiring is slowing, claims for unemployment benefits are rising, and consumers are retrenching, perhaps in response to uncertainty over tariffs and the government’s effort to cut spending.
